==English==

===Etymology===
From Old (and modern) French [[sacrer]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/seɪkə/}}

===Adjective===
'''sacre'''

#{{obsolete}} [[sacred]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#{{obsolete}} A [[religeous]] [[festival]]
#{{obsolete}} A [[consecration]], especially the [[coronation]] of a [[monarch]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|sacr|ing}}

# {{obsolete}} to [[consecrate]], especially with reference to the [[Eucharist]] or to a person of holy office such as a [[bishop]] or [[king]]
# {{obsolete}} to [[sanctify]], to make [[holy]]
# {{obsolete}} to [[dedicate]] to a [[god]], or by extension to another being or person

